Short answer: partial coverage already exists, and one small new Playwright test would meaningfully validate the multi-tenant fallback that isn't exercised today.

What is already covered (passively, just by running these after the change):

- [tests/homepage.spec.ts](apps/org-next/tests/homepage.spec.ts) — `tenants: []` → redirect to `/organizations/new`. Exercises `resolveSelectedTenantId` returning `null` when the user has no tenants.
- [tests/campaigns.spec.ts](apps/org-next/tests/campaigns.spec.ts) — single tenant `id: 42`, and the campaign requests are matched by `tenant_id=42` in the query string. This implicitly proves `resolveSelectedTenantId` persisted `42` into the cookie and that `currentTenant` flows through to campaign scoping. The vendor case proves the same for `id: 43`.

What is not covered:

- Multi-tenant with no cookie → pick the tenant with the greatest `updated_at` (central rule of the plan). The unit test covers the pure picker, but there is no end-to-end proof that `getAppBootstrapData` threads the chosen id into downstream API calls.
- Invalid stored id in the cookie → recover to most-recent. Same gap end-to-end.
- Theme round-trip. Not worth adding yet — nothing in the UI sets theme in this change.
- `useUserSession` client mutation. Same — no UI surface yet.

My recommendation: add one small spec that covers the multi-tenant most-recent fallback. The "invalid stored id" case is harder to set up (requires pre-seeding the signed cookie, which needs `SESSION_SECRET` knowledge and `useSession` sealing) and is already exercised by the unit test, so I'd skip it for now.

Proposed test (pseudocode, would live in a new `tests/user-session.spec.ts`):

```ts
await mockServerRequest.GET(usersApiPattern, { body: mockUser });
await mockServerRequest.GET(tenantsApiPattern, {
  body: [
    { ...tenantA, id: 1, updated_at: "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z" },
    { ...tenantB, id: 2, updated_at: "2025-06-01T00:00:00Z" }, // most recent
    { ...tenantC, id: 3, updated_at: "2024-12-01T00:00:00Z" },
  ],
});
await mockServerRequest.GET(
  /http:\/\/localhost:3210\/campaigns\?[^#]*tenant_id=2/,
  { body: [] },
);

